<svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 19, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104byr1665702625184.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/byr1665702625184.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/byr1665702625184.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"byr1665702625184\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">Compiled Module Information\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"byr1665702625184__compiled_module_information_63303\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The Compiled Module Inspector in the Write Script worksheet provides insight into the\n      code that is available in the runtime component. It displays a summary of the compiled modules\n      and their sources.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"byr1665702625184__note_w142ab1b5b5_w143ab1b5_w144ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The list of compiled modules is only\n         available after the component is compiled. If you make changes to any of the sources, these\n         will only be visible after the component is recompiled.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"byr1665702625184__p_d18608e1_d18609e1_d18610e1\">The ProcScript that is compiled into a runtime component\n         includes modules in the component itself, as well as modules that are inherited or included\n         from other sources. Some ProcScript modules may be excluded, and if duplicate modules are\n         defined, they are resolved.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"byr1665702625184__p_d18611e1_d18612e1_d18613e1\">Modules are listed as part of the object that determines\n         their visibility or scope. For example, entries are displayed at component level because\n         they have component-level visibility, even if they are defined in a lower-level object. An\n         entry defined at component level will overwritten by an entry with the same name defined at\n         field level; they cannot exist next to each other.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"byr1665702625184__p_d18614e1_d18615e1_d18616e1\">After compilation, the Compiled Modules Inspector:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"byr1665702625184__li_d8912e1_d8913e1_d8914e1\">Lists the compiled ProcScript modules for each object. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"byr1665702625184__li_d8915e1_d8916e1_d8917e1\">Indicates whether the compiled module is\n            locally-defined, inherited, or whether it overrides a module that is inherited or\n            defined elsewhere. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"byr1665702625184__li_d8918e1_d8919e1_d8920e1\">Enables you to navigate to the source of the compiled\n            object, whether that is somewhere in the component, or in another main development\n            object. </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"byr1665702625184__p_d18617e1_d18618e1_d18619e1\">To open the source of a compiled module, whether that is\n         in a modeled entity, an entry in a field, or in a component operation, double-click the\n         module name in the Modules list. The object contain the module is opened at the module\n         declaration.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"byr1665702625184__fig_d18620e1_d18621e1_d18622e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Compiled Modules Inspector </figcaption>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"byr1665702625184__fig_w137ab1b5c17b1b1_w138ab1b5c17b1_w139ab1b5c17_w140ab1b5_w141ab1\">\n<br/><img alt=\"Compiled Modules Inspector\" aria-label=\"Open image in gallery mode\" class=\"image expandable\" data-fancy=\"gallery\" data-gallery=\"gallery\" data-remote=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/compiledmodulestab.png?_LANG=enus\" data-title=\"\" role=\"button\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/compiledmodulestab.png?_LANG=enus\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"0\"/><br/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"byr1665702625184__li_d8921e1_d8922e1_d8923e1\">Compiled module information is shown for the\n               selected object, in this case a modeled component entity. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"byr1665702625184__li_d8924e1_d8925e1_d8926e1\">No local ProcScript is defined for the Lock, Read,\n               and other entity triggers ... </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"byr1665702625184__li_d8927e1_d8928e1_d8929e1\">... but the Compiled Modules Inspector shows that\n               trigger modules have been compiled. Icons indicate that these triggers were\n               inherited. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"byr1665702625184__li_d8930e1_d8931e1_d8932e1\">Although there is an entry defined for the component\n               entity, it is not shown here because entries have component scope, so it is only\n               visible when the Component is selected. </li>\n</ol>\n</figure>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Icons for Compiled Modules</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__1\"> Icon </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__2\"> Meaning </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e44\">\n<img alt=\"Local Function\" class=\"image\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e46\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/Proc-funtions.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__2\">Function is defined locally. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e62\">\n<img alt=\"Inherited Function\" class=\"image\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e64\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/Proc-function-inherited.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__2\"> Function is inherited.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e80\">\n<img alt=\"Inherited Function Operation\" class=\"image\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e82\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/proc_func_ol_inh.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__2\">Function replaces an inherited function.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e98\">\n<img alt=\"Overlay Function\" class=\"image\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e100\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/Proc_func_ol_in.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__2\"> Function replaces a function defined elsewhere,\n                     for example in an IncludeScript.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e116\">\n<img alt=\"Local Operation\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/proc_operation.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__2\"> Operation is defined locally. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e135\">\n<img alt=\"Inherited Operation\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/proc_operation_inh.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__2\">Operation is inherited.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e153\">\n<img alt=\"Inherited Overlay Operation\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/proc_operation_ol_inh.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__2\">Operation replaces an inherited\n\t\t\t\t operation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e171\">\n<img alt=\"Overlay Operation\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/proc_operation_ol.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__2\"> Operation replaces an operation defined\n\t\t\t\t elsewhere, for example in an IncludeScript.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e189\">\n<img alt=\"Local Trigger\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/proc_trigger.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__2\">Trigger is defined locally.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e207\">\n<img alt=\"Inherited Trigger\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/proc_trigger_inh.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__2\">Trigger is inherited.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e225\">\n<img alt=\"Inherited Overlay Trigger\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/proc_trigger_ol_inh.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__2\">Trigger replaces an inherited trigger.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e244\">\n<img alt=\"Overlay Trigger\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/proc_trigger_ol.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__2\"> Trigger replaces a trigger defined\n\t\t\t\t elsewhere, for example in an IncludeScript. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e262\">\n<img alt=\"Local Entry\" class=\"image\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e264\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/proc_entry.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__2\">Entry is defined locally. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e280\">\n<img alt=\"Inherited Entry\" class=\"image\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e282\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/proc_entry_inh.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__2\"> Entry is inherited.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e298\">\n<img alt=\"Inherited Overlay Entry\" class=\"image\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e300\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/proc_entry_ol_inh.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__2\">Entry replaces an inherited entry.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e316\">\n<img alt=\"Overlay Entry\" class=\"image\" id=\"byr1665702625184__d7002e318\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/proc_entry_ol.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"byr1665702625184__table_d2051e1_d2052e1_d2053e1__entry__2\">Entry replaces an entry defined in another object. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"byr1665702625184__topic_d13407e1_d13408e1_d13409e1_d13410e1_d13411e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d811876e432\"> CMI Files </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"byr1665702625184__p_d18626e1_d18627e1_d18628e1\">The compiler writes the compiled module information to\n               <span class=\"ph filepath\">*.cmi</span> files in the working directory.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"byr1665702625184__p_d18629e1_d18630e1_d18631e1\">If you want it in a different location, you can\n            redirect these files elsewhere, redirect them in the [FILES] section of the\n               <span class=\"ph filepath\">ide.asn</span> configuration file. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[FILES]\nusys:*.xml usysuniface:misc/*.xml\n*.cmi D:/Uniface/Uniface10_Data/project/cmi/*.cmi</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kwn1665702625105.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Inheritance</a><p>In Uniface, inheritance is a mechanism in which definitions in one development object are applied to other objects that re-use the definition. This makes it possible to define common behavior in one place instead of everywhere that it is used, making it much easier to maintain the application.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612273\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612273\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Compiled Module Information Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 19, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Compiled Module Information The Compiled Module Inspector in the Write Script worksheet provides insight into the code that is available in the runtime component. It displays a summary of the compiled modules and their sources. Note: The list of compiled modules is only available after the component is compiled. If you make changes to any of the sources, these will only be visible after the component is recompiled. The ProcScript that is compiled into a runtime component includes modules in the component itself, as well as modules that are inherited or included from other sources. Some ProcScript modules may be excluded, and if duplicate modules are defined, they are resolved. Modules are listed as part of the object that determines their visibility or scope. For example, entries are displayed at component level because they have component-level visibility, even if they are defined in a lower-level object. An entry defined at component level will overwritten by an entry with the same name defined at field level; they cannot exist next to each other. After compilation, the Compiled Modules Inspector: Lists the compiled ProcScript modules for each object. Indicates whether the compiled module is locally-defined, inherited, or whether it overrides a module that is inherited or defined elsewhere. Enables you to navigate to the source of the compiled object, whether that is somewhere in the component, or in another main development object. To open the source of a compiled module, whether that is in a modeled entity, an entry in a field, or in a component operation, double-click the module name in the Modules list. The object contain the module is opened at the module declaration. Figure 1. Compiled Modules Inspector Compiled module information is shown for the selected object, in this case a modeled component entity. No local ProcScript is defined for the Lock, Read, and other entity triggers ... ... but the Compiled Modules Inspector shows that trigger modules have been compiled. Icons indicate that these triggers were inherited. Although there is an entry defined for the component entity, it is not shown here because entries have component scope, so it is only visible when the Component is selected. Table 1. Icons for Compiled Modules Icon Meaning Function is defined locally. Function is inherited. Function replaces an inherited function. Function replaces a function defined elsewhere, for example in an IncludeScript. Operation is defined locally. Operation is inherited. Operation replaces an inherited operation. Operation replaces an operation defined elsewhere, for example in an IncludeScript. Trigger is defined locally. Trigger is inherited. Trigger replaces an inherited trigger. Trigger replaces a trigger defined elsewhere, for example in an IncludeScript. Entry is defined locally. Entry is inherited. Entry replaces an inherited entry. Entry replaces an entry defined in another object. CMI Files The compiler writes the compiled module information to *.cmi files in the working directory. If you want it in a different location, you can redirect these files elsewhere, redirect them in the [FILES] section of the ide.asn configuration file. For example: [FILES] usys:*.xml usysuniface:misc/*.xml *.cmi D:/Uniface/Uniface10_Data/project/cmi/*.cmi Copy Related Links Inheritance In Uniface, inheritance is a mechanism in which definitions in one development object are applied to other objects that re-use the definition. This makes it possible to define common behavior in one place instead of everywhere that it is used, making it much easier to maintain the application. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}